  "prompt": "Why do some people hate Shahrukh Khan so much?",
  "response": "Shahrukh Khan, often referred to as the \"King of Bollywood,\" is a highly successful and influential actor in India and around the world. However, like any public figure, he also has critics and detractors. Here are some reasons why some people might dislike him:\n\n1. **Overexposure**: Shahrukh Khan has been a dominant figure in Bollywood for decades, starring in numerous films and appearing frequently on television and in the media. Some people might feel that he is overexposed and that his constant presence becomes overwhelming.\n\n2. **Political Views**: Shahrukh Khan has expressed his views on various social and political issues, including intolerance and human rights. These views have sometimes put him at odds with certain political groups or individuals who disagree with his stance.\n\n3. **Perceived Arrogance**: Some people perceive Shahrukh Khan as arrogant or overly confident due to his successful career and high public profile. This perception can lead to negative feelings towards him.\n\n4. **Acting Style and Film Choices**: Not everyone appreciates Shahrukh Khan's acting style or the types of films he chooses to star in. Some critics argue that his roles are repetitive or that he relies too heavily on romantic dramas.\n\n5. **Controversies**: Like many celebrities, Shahrukh Khan has been involved in various controversies over the years, ranging from legal issues to public disputes. These incidents can shape public opinion and lead to negative sentiments.\n\n6. **Fan Wars**: In the entertainment industry, fan rivalries are common. Some fans of other actors might express dislike for Shahrukh Khan simply because they prefer another celebrity.\n\nIt's important to note that these reasons vary widely and not everyone who dislikes Shahrukh Khan does so for the same reason. Public opinion is diverse, and individuals have their own personal reasons for their feelings towards celebrities.",
